properties.areaDesc: Coastal waters from Chincoteague to Parramore Island VA out 20 nm; Coastal waters from Fenwick Island DE to Chincoteague VA out 20 nm
properties.headline: Gale Warning issued January 15 at 1:45PM EST until January 17 at 10:00AM EST by NWS Wakefield VA
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Gale Warning, northwest winds 25 to 35 kt with
gusts up to 40 kt. Seas 5 to 7 ft. For the Small Craft
Advisory, northwest winds 20 to 30 kt. Seas 3 to 6 ft.

* WHERE...Coastal waters from Fenwick Island DE to Chincoteague
VA out 20 nm and Coastal waters from Chincoteague to Parramore
Island VA out 20 nm.

* WHEN...For the Gale Warning, from 6 PM Thursday to 10 AM EST
Friday. For the Small Craft Advisory, from 10 AM to 6 PM EST
Thursday.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds will cause hazardous waves which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should alter plans to avoid these hazardous conditions.
Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter course, and/or secure the
vessel for severe conditions.

NWSheadline: SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 10 AM TO 6 PM EST THURSDAY... ...GALE WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 6 PM THURSDAY TO 10 AM EST FRIDAY
